  "texts": [
    "• The Geometric Mean (G-Mean) is another performance metric that comprehensively evaluates a model's accuracy by combining sensitivity and specificity.",
    "It is commonly employed in scenarios involving imbalanced datasets.",
    "G-mean is defined as the geometric mean of sensitivity and specificity:",
    "By considering sensitivity and specificity, the G-Mean offers a balanced assessment of a classifier's performance on both minority and majority classes.",
    "It provides a reliable measure of accuracy, accounting for the occurrence of FP and FN."
  ],
